    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[ErPr61] Erd\\H{o}s, P. and Prachar, K., S\\\"{a}tze und {P}robleme \\\"{u}ber {$p\\sb{k}/k$}. Abh. Math. Sem. Univ. Hamburg (1961/62), 251--256.",
      "remarks": "Erd\\H{o}s and Prachar \\cite{ErPr61} proved that\\[\\sum_{p_n<x} \\lvert u_{n+1}-u_n\\rvert \\asymp (\\log x)^2,\\]and that the set of $n$ such that $u_n>u_{n+1}$ has positive density.\n\nAs with many of Erd\\H{o}s' questions, by 'positive density' here he most likely meant positive lower density - in other words, there exists a constant $c>0$ such that for all large $x$ the number of such $n\\leq x$ is at least $cx$.\n\nErd\\H{o}s also asks whether\\[u_n<u_{n+1}<u_{n+2}\\]or\\[u_n>u_{n+1}>u_{n+2}\\]have infinitely many solutions."
    },
